UserRegistrationDelegate

@protocol UserRegistrationDelegate <NSObject>

Use this delegate to receive callbacks about user registration, login, forgot passowrd, resend verfication, account merging and logout events.

@since 1.0.0

  • -didLoginWithSuccessWithUser:

    Called when user has been authenticated successfully.

    @discussion This callback does not gaurantee that user login process has completed. User might not have accepted TnC of application. This callback merely indicates that user’s authentication with backend was successful. @since 1.0.0

  • -handleAccountSocailMergeWithExistingAccountProvider:provider:

    Called when user is trying to login with one provider while user’s account already exists with different provider. In such case, user need to merge the accounts to be able to login with both providers or go back to provider with which the account was originally created.

    @since 1.0.0

    Declaration

    Objective-C

                                                   provider:(nonnull NSString *)
                                                                provider;

    Swift

    optional func handleAccountSocailMerge(withExistingAccountProvider existingAccountProvider: String, provider: String)

    Parameters

    existingAccountProvider

    Name of the provider with which user is already registered.
    provider

    Name of the provider with which user is trying to login.
